    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the meatballs are starting to brown, add the <strong>sliced garlic</strong>, <strong>dried oregano</strong> and <strong>dried basil</strong> to the pan with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp] </span><strong>flour</strong> and cook for 30 secs or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>tomato stock </strong>to the pan and cook for 2-3 min or until the sauce has thickened slightly and the meatballs are cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
